 Business Briefs

 New York, April 19: The Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) has slapped show-cause notices to 12 entities for alleged price manipulation that led to the market crash in 2004. It has also asked stock exchanges to furnish trading data to find out whether there was a market manipulation on Friday when the sensex crashed by over 219 points and wiped out more than Rs 50,000 crore of investors? wealth, said M. Damodaran, Sebi chief.

 New York, April 19: The government is keen to expedite the process of full capital-account convertibility as well as enable banks to take more risks for stepping up credit to agriculture and services sectors, said Rakesh Mohan, economic affairs secretary.

 New Delhi, April 19: The government today issued a notification prescribing the conditions and procedures for the export of services without the payment of service tax. 

 New Delhi, April 19: Jubilant Organosys board has approved the allotment of 21,903 shares of Rs 5 each at a premium of Rs 813.23 per share to ABN Amro Bank NV.

 New Delhi, April 19: The government is planning to unveil a relief package for the coffee sector in the current budget session.




